With my companies current setup we are opening and closing browsers hundreds of times during testing. As you could imagine doing this over and over takes up a lot of unnecessary time. I currently have a semi-working version of a `Reset Browser` keyword. Currently this keyword will close all extra tabs that are open and remove all cookies from all unique domains that were visited during testing. 

One issue I came across while creating this keyword was that currently `Remove All Cookies` only removes the cookies on the current domain. I was able to work around this by storing the current domain whenever we expected a page change and then having the `Reset Browser` keyword loop through each unique domain visited and remove the cookies.

Would it be possible to add the ability to keep track of all of the domains visited during the current session? Or a keyword that would remove all cookies across all the domains that were visited.

Here is what the keyword looks like so far. 
```
@{domains visited}=  Get Domains Visited  @{pages visited}
    @{pages visited}=  Create List  ${EMPTY}
    :FOR  ${domain}  IN  @{domains visited}
    \  Go to  ${domain}
    \  Delete All Cookies
    @{windows}=  List Windows
    ${total windows}=  Get Length  ${windows}
    Run Keyword If  ${total windows}==1  Return From Keyword
    :For  ${window}  IN RANGE  ${total windows-1}
    \  Close Window
    \  Select Window  main
```

